---
import BaseLayout from '@layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About CalcFalcon | Free Calculators for Freelancers & Creators"
  description="CalcFalcon provides free, privacy-first financial calculators for freelancers, creators, gig workers, and side hustlers."
>
  <div class="py-16">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4">
      <h1 class="heading-lg mb-8">About CalcFalcon</h1>

      <div class="prose prose-neutral prose-lg max-w-none">
        <p>
          CalcFalcon builds free financial calculators for people who work for themselves. Whether you're a freelancer setting rates, a creator tracking platform earnings, a gig worker estimating take-home pay, or someone building a side hustle toward a financial goal, our tools help you make smarter money decisions.
        </p>

        <h2>Who It's For</h2>
        <p>
          Traditional financial tools are built for salaried employees with predictable paychecks. That doesn't work when your income varies by month, your tax situation involves self-employment calculations, or your expenses include platform fees and business costs that most calculators ignore.
        </p>
        <p>
          CalcFalcon is built specifically for:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Freelancers and consultants</strong> who need to set hourly or project rates that actually cover taxes, expenses, and profit</li>
          <li><strong>Content creators</strong> on YouTube, Twitch, Patreon, Substack, Etsy, and Ko-fi who want to understand their real earnings after platform fees</li>
          <li><strong>Gig economy workers</strong> on DoorDash, Uber, Lyft, Instacart, and Airbnb who need to factor in vehicle costs, time, and taxes</li>
          <li><strong>Side hustlers</strong> planning their path from extra income to a sustainable business</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>How Our Calculators Work</h2>
        <p>
          Every calculator on CalcFalcon runs entirely in your browser. Your numbers never leave your device — there's no account to create, no data stored on our servers, and no tracking of your financial inputs. When you close the tab, your data is gone.
        </p>
        <p>
          Each calculator offers two modes: <strong>Quick mode</strong> for fast estimates with sensible defaults, and <strong>Advanced mode</strong> for detailed analysis when precision matters. Results can be shared via URL — the calculator state is encoded directly in the link, so the recipient sees exactly what you see without any server-side storage.
        </p>

        <h2>Why We Built This</h2>
        <p>
          The independent workforce is growing, but the financial tools haven't kept up. Most "freelance rate calculators" online are marketing funnels for accounting software or oversimplified tools that miss critical factors like self-employment tax, quarterly estimated payments, or platform-specific fee structures.
        </p>
        <p>
          CalcFalcon exists to fill that gap with tools that are genuinely useful, totally free, and respect your privacy. No paywalls, no email gates, no "schedule a demo" buttons. Just calculators that work.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
